transcript.text: Welcome to on Print Shop.
In this video we will be talking about how you can create associated products.
Associated products are a great way to offer a great shopping experience.
This also saves time in searching and adding other products that are most likely bought together.
Let's have a look at the storefront.
When a customer wants to purchase a banner product and opts to add a banner stand, they can select yes and the Do you want to add a banner stand?
And the associated product will appear with its pricing and subtotal.
And additionally, it will be added to the shopping cart automatically.
Now let's go to the admin panel and see how you can configure an associated product.
First of all, we need to go to the products section and click on the predefined products menu.
Let's create an associated product called the banner stand by clicking on the Add button.
Here you need to mention the product title.
Choose a price defining method, enable the status and configure the other fields as per your requirements.
Click on Save and Continue.
In the next screen, upload the small and large images, add some details about the banner stand and then click on Save and Continue.
You will be redirected to the next important screen which is the pricing tab.
Enter the quantity as per the pricing method selected.
We have selected fixed quantity and price.
So let us just add some quantity and pricing for the same.
Once done, click on Save and continue.
You can define other details from the rest of the tabs as per your business needs.
So after the product setup, it is now time to create a product or master option for this.
From the left navigation panel, move to the Product options menu and then click on the Add button.
On the Add screen, add the title for the option.
Select the option type, define the pricing if required and Scroll down to the attribute section.
Add 2 attributes as Yes or No and then click on Save and back from the top right corner.
From the main product option listing screen, you can find a button named Associate Product on the top right corner of the screen.
We are at the final step of creating the associated product which is associating the predefined product we created with the product option and the main product.
To do so, click on the Associate Product button and then click on the Add button.
Here, enter the title of the associate product.
Select the product option we recently created with the value yes and enter the quantity multiplier value in the space provided.
This multiplier will add the relevant quantity of the associated product to the main product.
Suppose that you need to stand with one single banner which double S the quantity of the associate product.
Then add to here.
After adding a multiplier, it is time to select the associated product, the predefined product we created.
So we have selected Banner stand.
Here activate the status of this product and click on Save.
Lastly, let's go to the product listing page.
Search for the main product which is banner and go to its Options tab.
Here click on the Assign Product Options button.
On the next screen, locate the Do you want to add a banner stand option?
Select the attributes and click on Save.
Now we have successfully associated both products on the front store.
You can see that when the customer is on the banner details page, there is this.
Do you want to add banner stand option And on the selection of yes to banner stands have been added as per the configuration we made.
That's it.
This is how you can create products and associate them to ease the shopping experience of your customers.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
